{"id":12067,"date":"2022-03-14T05:19:47","date_gmt":"2022-03-14T05:19:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=12067"},"modified":"2022-03-14T05:19:52","modified_gmt":"2022-03-14T05:19:52","slug":"fire-through-dry-grass","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/fire-through-dry-grass\/","title":{"rendered":"Fire Through Dry Grass"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"12068\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/fire-through-dry-grass\/fire-through-dry-grass\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?fit=1280%2C346&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1280,346\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Fire Through Dry Grass\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"&lt;p&gt;Photo credit: Elias Williams&lt;\/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?fit=300%2C81&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?fit=800%2C216&amp;ssl=1\" fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"800\" height=\"216\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?resize=800%2C216&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Five Black and brown men (from left to right: Vince, Jay, Tito, Pete and Var) sit in wheelchairs outside, all lined up in a straight horizontal line facing the camera. They wear T-shirts and sneakers and some wear baseball caps. They all look into the camera with serious expressions.\" class=\"wp-image-12068\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?resize=1024%2C277&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?resize=300%2C81&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?resize=768%2C208&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/fire-through-dry-grass.png?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption>Photo credit: Elias Williams<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Jay (second from left) is Co-Director of an upcoming documentary,\u00a0<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/urldefense.proofpoint.com\/v2\/url?u=https-3A__www.firethroughdrygrass.com_&amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;c=slrrB7dE8n7gBJbeO0g-IQ&amp;r=OohFqohqX3-QojZB4dO5k47Ylk_pygWz1WB60GXeyw0&amp;m=9MXV-OZGjNcPyYKDNOYAkms144PRTBLV-kU1aKHleHa183GVLczi7dQadXMdX18S&amp;s=MQkw6ZgTmBwz0f8sCj7Omh10pnC9Uh18PsvnTg-BoHw&amp;e=\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Fire Through Dry Grass<\/em><\/a><em>,\u00a0<\/em>that is centered on a group of people living at Coler Specialty Hospital on Roosevelt Island, a rehabilitation and nursing center in New York City.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These men formed\u00a0<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/urldefense.proofpoint.com\/v2\/url?u=https-3A__www.opendoorsnyc.org_reality-2Dpoets&amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;c=slrrB7dE8n7gBJbeO0g-IQ&amp;r=OohFqohqX3-QojZB4dO5k47Ylk_pygWz1WB60GXeyw0&amp;m=9MXV-OZGjNcPyYKDNOYAkms144PRTBLV-kU1aKHleHa183GVLczi7dQadXMdX18S&amp;s=iqk3RBMBQEuyQL9JWfHJSmcxQdeLS77MIQD8YRiqWws&amp;e=\" target=\"_blank\">the Reality Poets<\/a>, and are part of\u00a0<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/urldefense.proofpoint.com\/v2\/url?u=https-3A__www.opendoorsnyc.org_&amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;c=slrrB7dE8n7gBJbeO0g-IQ&amp;r=OohFqohqX3-QojZB4dO5k47Ylk_pygWz1WB60GXeyw0&amp;m=9MXV-OZGjNcPyYKDNOYAkms144PRTBLV-kU1aKHleHa183GVLczi7dQadXMdX18S&amp;s=nyoxA47aMjBbpOw6ekmsz9MtuilNMy8wFEjydKY6viY&amp;e=\" target=\"_blank\">OPEN DOORS<\/a>, a network of artists, activists and advocates motivated by community building, gun violence prevention and disability rights, a collective of truth-telling artists bonded through a shared mission to spread a message of realness, resilience and healing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Fire Through Dry Grass\u00a0<\/em>paints a human-scale portrait of the devastation inflicted upon American nursing home residents during the coronavirus pandemic, in particular people of color, immigrants, and formerly incarcerated people.\u00a0The circumstances they are documenting show how toxic ideas that certain lives matter less, and are a threat, have penetrated long-term care.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Watch the Trailer<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Fire Through Dry Grass &amp;ndash; Trailer\" src=\"https:\/\/player.vimeo.com\/video\/446557890?h=d695bbf50b&amp;dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more about <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.firethroughdrygrass.com\/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Fire Through Dr<\/em><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.firethroughdrygrass.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><em>y<\/em><\/a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.firethroughdrygrass.com\/\" target=\"_blank\"><em> Grass<\/em><\/a>.<\/p>\n","